An Angel at My Table;;1990;;R;;Biography,Drama;;7.5;;Jane Campion;;Kerry Fox,Alexia Keogh,Karen Fergusson,Iris Churn,Jessie Mune,Kevin J. Wilson,Francesca Collins,Melina Bernecker,Mark Morrison,Katherine Murray-Cowper,Mark Thomson,Brenda Kendall,Paul Moffat,Blair Hutchison,David McAuslan,Ailene Herring,Faye Flegg,Carla Hedgeman;;In 1920s and 1930s New Zealand, Janet Frame grows up in a poor family with lots of brothers and sisters. Already at an early age she is different from the other kids. She gets an education as a teacher but since she is considered abnormal she stays at a mental institution for eight years. Success comes when she starts to write novels.;;https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0099040/